121 struct PlayerSpell
122 {
123  PlayerSpellState State : 7; // UPPER CASE TO CAUSE CONSOLE ERRORS (CHECK EVERY USAGE)!
124  bool Active : 1; // UPPER CASE TO CAUSE CONSOLE ERRORS (CHECK EVERY USAGE)! lower rank of a spell are not useable, but learnt
125  uint8 specMask : 8;
126  bool IsInSpec(uint8 spec) { return (specMask & (1 << spec)); }
127 };

175 struct SpellModifier
176 {

243 #define ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(X) (uint32(X) & 0x00FFFFFF)
244 #define ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(X) ((uint32(X) & 0xFF000000) >> 24)
245 #define MAX_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION_VALUE (0x00FFFFFF+1)
246 
247 struct ActionButton
248 {
249  ActionButton() {}
250 
251  uint32 packedData{0};
252  ActionButtonUpdateState uState{ACTIONBUTTON_NEW};
253 
254  // helpers
255  [[nodiscard]] ActionButtonType GetType() const { return ActionButtonType(ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(packedData)); }
256  [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetAction() const { return ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData); }
257  void SetActionAndType(uint32 action, ActionButtonType type)
258  {
259  uint32 newData = action | (uint32(type) << 24);
260  if (newData != packedData || uState == ACTIONBUTTON_DELETED)
261  {
262  packedData = newData;
263  if (uState != ACTIONBUTTON_NEW)
264  uState = ACTIONBUTTON_CHANGED;
265  }
266  }
267 };
268

408 struct Runes
409 {
410  RuneInfo runes[MAX_RUNES];
411  uint8 runeState; // mask of available runes
412  RuneType lastUsedRune;
413 
414  void SetRuneState(uint8 index, bool set = true)
415  {
416  if (set)
417  runeState |= (1 << index); // usable
418  else
419  runeState &= ~(1 << index); // on cooldown
420  }
421 };

1417  [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetQuestSlotQuestId(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_ID_OFFSET); }
1418  [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetQuestSlotState(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET); }
1419  [[nodiscard]] uint16 GetQuestSlotCounter(uint16 slot, uint8 counter) const { return (uint16)(GetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET) >> (counter * 16)); }
1420  [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetQuestSlotTime(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET); }
1421  void SetQuestSlot(uint16 slot, uint32 quest_id, uint32 timer = 0)
1422  {
1423  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_ID_OFFSET, quest_id);
1424  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, 0);
1425  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET, 0);
1426  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET + 1, 0);
1427  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET, timer);
1428  }
1429  void SetQuestSlotCounter(uint16 slot, uint8 counter, uint16 count)
1430  {
1431  uint64 val = GetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET);
1432  val &= ~((uint64)0xFFFF << (counter * 16));
1433  val |= ((uint64)count << (counter * 16));
1434  SetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET, val);
1435  }
1436  void SetQuestSlotState(uint16 slot, uint32 state) { SetFlag(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, state); }
1437  void RemoveQuestSlotState(uint16 slot, uint32 state) { RemoveFlag(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, state); }
1438  void SetQuestSlotTimer(uint16 slot, uint32 timer) { SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET, timer); }
1439  void SwapQuestSlot(uint16 slot1, uint16 slot2)
1440  {
1441  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_QUEST_OFFSET; ++i)
1442  {
1443  uint32 temp1 = GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot1 + i);
1444  uint32 temp2 = GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot2 + i);
1445 
1446  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot1 + i, temp2);
1447  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot2 + i, temp1);
1448  }
1449  }

1544  if (amount > 0)
1545  return (GetMoney() >= (uint32) amount);
1546  return true;
1547  }

1721  [[nodiscard]] bool HasSpellCooldown(uint32 spell_id) const override

1727  {
1728  SpellCooldowns::const_iterator itr = m_spellCooldowns.find(spell_id);
1729  return itr != m_spellCooldowns.end() && itr->second.end > World::GetGameTimeMS() && itr->second.itemid == itemid;
1730  }

1734  return uint32(itr != m_spellCooldowns.end() && itr->second.end > World::GetGameTimeMS() ? itr->second.end - World::GetGameTimeMS() : 0);
1735  }

2953 
2954 // "the bodies of template functions must be made available in a header file"
2955 template <class T> T Player::ApplySpellMod(uint32 spellId, SpellModOp op, T& basevalue, Spell* spell, bool temporaryPet)
2956 {
2957  SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(spellId);
2958  if (!spellInfo)
2959  return 0;
2960  float totalmul = 1.0f;
2961  int32 totalflat = 0;
2962 
2963  // Drop charges for triggering spells instead of triggered ones
2964  if (m_spellModTakingSpell)
2965  spell = m_spellModTakingSpell;
2966 
2967  for (auto mod : m_spellMods[op])
2968  {
2969  // Charges can be set only for mods with auras
2970  if (!mod->ownerAura)
2971  ASSERT(mod->charges == 0);
2972 
2973  if (!IsAffectedBySpellmod(spellInfo, mod, spell))
2974  continue;
2975 
2976  // xinef: temporary pets cannot use charged mods of owner, needed for mirror image QQ they should use their own auras
2977  if (temporaryPet && mod->charges != 0)
2978  continue;
2979 
2980  if (mod->type == SPELLMOD_FLAT)
2981  {
2982  // xinef: do not allow to consume more than one 100% crit increasing spell
2983  if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CRITICAL_CHANCE && totalflat >= 100)
2984  continue;
2985 
2986  totalflat += mod->value;
2987  }
2988  else if (mod->type == SPELLMOD_PCT)
2989  {
2990  // skip percent mods for null basevalue (most important for spell mods with charges)
2991  if (basevalue == T(0) || totalmul == 0.0f)
2992  continue;
2993 
2994  // special case (skip > 10sec spell casts for instant cast setting)
2995  if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CASTING_TIME && basevalue >= T(10000) && mod->value <= -100)
2996  continue;
2997  // xinef: special exception for surge of light, dont affect crit chance if previous mods were not applied
2998  else if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CRITICAL_CHANCE && spell && !HasSpellMod(mod, spell))
2999  continue;
3000  // xinef: special case for backdraft gcd reduce with backlast time reduction, dont affect gcd if cast time was not applied
3001  else if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_GLOBAL_COOLDOWN && spell && !HasSpellMod(mod, spell))
3002  continue;
3003 
3004  // xinef: those two mods should be multiplicative (Glyph of Renew)
3005  if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_DAMAGE || mod->op == SPELLMOD_DOT)
3006  totalmul *= CalculatePct(1.0f, 100.0f + mod->value);
3007  else
3008  totalmul += CalculatePct(1.0f, mod->value);
3009  }
3010 
3011  DropModCharge(mod, spell);
3012  }
3013  float diff = 0.0f;
3014  if (op == SPELLMOD_CASTING_TIME || op == SPELLMOD_DURATION)
3015  diff = ((float)basevalue + totalflat) * (totalmul - 1.0f) + (float)totalflat;
3016  else
3017  diff = (float)basevalue * (totalmul - 1.0f) + (float)totalflat;
3018  basevalue = T((float)basevalue + diff);
3019  return T(diff);
3020 }
3021 #endif
